          <td class="NewsTitle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><br>
            Poll result - Should we raise the min. level?&nbsp;&nbsp; <span class="NewsUser">Errol 
            - 24-10-2000 at 12:19:03</span> 
            <br>
		  <span class="NewsTitleDescription">The results are in and the Council has made a decision on the issue...</span>
		  </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="32" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsText" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
            <br>
			Should we raise the minimum level required to join the Aegis Lux?<br><br>Two weeks ago a poll was posted, trying to measure the oppinion regarding this. At the same time long threads on the Private Board discussed the topic in great detail.<br><br>Heres the result of the poll:<br><br><b>Yes - We should raise the level to 20 = 17 votes or 29 %<br><br>Yes - We should raise the level to 25 = 4 votes or 7 %<br><br>Yes - We should raise the level to 30 = 9 votes or 16 %<br><br>No - We should keep the level at 10 = 23 votes or 40 %<br><br>I don't care = 5 votes or 9 %</b><br><br>It is clear that people were divided on the issue and the poll can be interpreted in many ways.<br><br>I have chosen to combine both the poll results, the posts on the boards and the many tells and /gu's on the issue. Many new members well above level 20 has also played a part in my decision, which can be summarized like this:<br><br><b>The minimum level requirement for new applicants to the Aegis Lux is now raised from level 10 to level 20.</b><br><br>On what basis you might ask? Well, friends, I urge you to go and read my post in the Private Forum.
          </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
