          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsTitle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><br>
            New Class Leader -- Warriors!&nbsp;&nbsp; <span class="NewsUser">Errol 
            - 14-10-2000 at 12:43:25</span> 
            <br>
		  <span class="NewsTitleDescription">Arthun the Battle Dwarf is in a semi-retired state and new blood was needed...</span>
		  </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="32" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsText" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
            <br>
			<i>"...Arthun had grown somewhat weary of the road. He needed some time in solitude to reflect upon his life and the ways of Norrath. It had been a long time since he had set foot in Kaladim, pride of the Undermountains. The incessant din of hammers on anvils and the stomping of booted feet, was like sweet music to his ears.<br><br>Arthun kicked open the gate to the Warriors Guild and roared "Nussback - you old coot! Where are ye? I am back!". <br><br>Stomping through the stone halls, he turned a corner and found Canloe Nussback standing in front of the fire in one of the back-rooms of the guild. The table in front of him was strewn with orcish shoulderpads and belts.<br><br>"Still got a passion for those trinkets I see?" Arthun grinned and grabbed the plate-armored dwarf in a bearhug. Canloe blinked confused at Arthun and managed to stutter a few words of greeting, before Arthun had squeezed all the air outta him. Arthun finally put the poor dwarf down and Canloe grabbed his friends shoulders to steady himself. <br><br>"But, Art..what are ye doing here? Last time I heard ye were in Soluseks Eye trying to get me one of them Dragon Armors I wanted" Canloe sputtered still heaving for breath...<br><br>"True..", Arthun said, throwing himself in one of the large armchairs in front of the fireplace. "But I got tired of bashing kobolds, while waiting for Naggy to return. Brell know where he's hiding these days..Probably heard me coming and fluttered off, damn overgrown lizzard".<br><br>Arthun cursed and leaned his Wurmslayer against the table. "I need some time to think, thats all. And I thought I could do it here?". Arthun eyed Canloe, who pulled up a second chair. "Off course ye, can ye rock-head" Canloe said "But who's fer minding the Warriors of the Shield?".<br><br>Arthun smiled at that remark. And his grin spread all across his bearded face, when he turned to Canloe and mumbled "..oh, I do believe I got that covered, friend..Don't worry..."</i><br><br>All hail our new Warrior Class Leader:<br><br><b>Durgin Bugman</b><br><br>Congratulations Durgster.<br><br>Now, go make us proud!
          </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
