          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsTitle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><br>
            Applicants for 1st. Circle have not been forgotten&nbsp;&nbsp; <span class="NewsUser">Errol 
            - 01-10-2000 at 18:15:18</span> 
            <br>
		  <span class="NewsTitleDescription">The Council is acutely aware of the applicants who are vying for 1st. Circle.</span>
		  </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="32" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsText" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
            <br>
			<i>"...You will never know when it is your turn. It could be today or it could be a week from now. Who you are, what you have done. This is what determines when you will be deemed worthy.<br><br>You will get no date. Such is not the way of the Gods or the way of Norrath. Ever shifting is Darkness and we must evolve with it or be swallowed up. Be alert, brothers and sisters, is all I can say. It may be that ye have all the trinkets or have seen the correct number of seasons through, to apply for the title, but who says that is all? Do not be so proud that ye think the world revolves around you!<br><br>By the Councils decree, by the 5 Basic Truths and by the Gods - keep yer eyes and ears open. The day when ye have to stand up to yer beliefs may come sooner than ye like..."</i><br><br><b>- Errol</b><br><br>/OOC Let me personally say that it is simply terrific that so many feels they are ready for 1st. Circle. It shows a dedication we could only hope for. I salute each and every one of you. You have my deepest respect and admiration. <br>We want this done right. And we want it to mean something to graduate to 1st. Circle. That is why it is taking so long for some applicants to recieve an "answer".<br><br>And believe me, answers will not be given in a straight-forward manner. No, "yes" or "no" will be issued. People who are lacking will be informed why and how to better themselves, but by means of roleplay.<br><br>Applicants for 1st. Circle need to be patient, as well as exhibiting all the other virtues in the 5 Truths.<br><br>Now show the Council the courtesy of being patient. Roleplaying is not about timetables and dates.<br>
          </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
